data.title: About: Deylaman District
data.meta_description: Deylaman District (Persian: بخش دیلمان) is a district (bakhsh) in Siahkal County, Gilan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 12,721, in 3,650 families. The District has one city: Deylaman. The District has two rural districts (dehestan): Deylaman Rural District and Pir Kuh Rural District.
data.text:
dbo:abstract

Deylaman District (Persian: بخش دیلمان) is a district (bakhsh) in Siahkal County, Gilan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 12,721, in 3,650 families. The District has one city: Deylaman. The District has two rural districts (dehestan): Deylaman Rural District and Pir Kuh Rural District. (en)

La Circoscrizione di Deylaman farsi دیلمان, è un bakhsh (circoscrizione) situato nello Shahrestān di Siahkal, nella Provincia di Gilan.
